                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Keeping your home warm in the winter is essential to ensure the comfort&nbsp;and good health of your household. If you have a furnace, you should be able to&nbsp;sustain a comfortably warm home without spending an unreasonable amount on&nbsp;utility bills in the process. <a href="/about-us" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">East</a>&nbsp;<a href="/about-us" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">Side Ventilation</a> is happy to help you with all your furnace needs, from installation to maintenance, and furnace repair in your Winnipeg home.</p> </div>
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p><br></p><p>Do not forget to&nbsp;book a furnace tune-up on a yearly basis. This one simple step could help to&nbsp;save you much money over the course of your furnace’s lifespan.&nbsp;</p><p><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">How Annual Furnace Tune-ups Can Work to Your Advantage</span><br><br>If you are unsure about why you should have your furnace tuned up annually, read on for 5 top reasons that furnace maintenance is so important:<br><br>1.<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Safety Concerns</span> – The most critical reason to book yearly maintenance visits is the opportunity to identify and correct potential safety issues. A trained professional will check your furnace to ensure that it is running properly. This inspection is vital because it<br>could reveal issues with the connections or a ventilation problem, for example. The best time to do this is before the temperatures plummet and you need to rely on your furnace for basic warmth. A service visit also gives the technician a chance to check for gas leaks if you have a gas furnace, and this can save lives.<br><br>2. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Preventative Action</span> – In many cases, furnace tuning is a preventative measure that can help you avoid future repairs. By catching problems early, our technicians can often correct them so that they do not grow into major issues. <br><br>3. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Emergency Repairs</span> – By detecting and fixing issues sooner rather than later, we may also prevent the need for an emergency repair visit. One of the most common and inconvenient times for a furnace to break down is during the colder months of the year. We always arrive as quickly as possible, but the busy season may lead to longer wait times for parts. It is far better to catch an issue and fix it before the height of the furnace <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-repair-replacement-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">repair season</a>. <br><br>4. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Longevity</span> – By keeping your furnace in good condition with routine <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-cleaning-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">cleaning and service</a> visits, you may also increase its lifespan. This means you will save money because you won’t need to replace this essential appliance as often as you otherwise would. <br><br>5. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Efficiency</span> – Another top benefit of yearly tune-ups is that when your furnace is clean and in good shape, it will run better on a consistent basis. It will also be more energy efficient, which is beneficial to both your budget and the environment. <br><br>At East Side Ventilation, we take pride in helping local customers meet their HVAC needs. We can perform annual maintenance visits on your furnace, so you will not be forced to pay for expensive repairs later that could have been avoided. <br><br>Contact us to book a furnace tuning visit in your Winnipeg home. You can reach us at <a data-global="phone" href="tel:204-667-8700" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="phone_link">204-667-8700</a>. Also, feel free to fill out our quick <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">online contact form</a>.</p> </div>
